  "title": "Wealth Adviser (Leads Supported)",
  "description": "<p>Considering a mid-career switch into financial services? This role offers a structured entry into financial advisory with leads support, fixed monthly remuneration, and high commission and incentive potential. Whether you are transitioning from banking, sales, or a non-finance background, comprehensive training and mentorship will be provided.<br /><br /><br /><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provide financial advisory solutions tailored to clients’ needs</p></li><li><p>Conduct fact-finding sessions to understand clients’ financial objectives</p></li><li><p>Analyse client information and recommend suitable strategies and solutions</p></li><li><p>Manage and grow a client portfolio with ongoing reviews and follow-ups</p></li><li><p>Build long-term client relationships through professional service</p></li><li><p>Adhere strictly to regulatory and compliance standards<br /></p></li></ul><h3><strong>What We Offer</strong></h3><ul><li><p><strong>Fixed monthly pay package</strong> with <strong>high incentives and uncapped commissions</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Leads supported</strong> to help you build momentum and close cases</p></li><li><p>Structured training and one-to-one mentorship</p></li><li><p>Clear career progression pathway</p></li><li><p>Supportive team culture suited for career switchers<br /></p></li></ul><h3><strong>Who This Role Is For</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Mid-career professionals exploring a stable yet rewarding career switch</p></li><li><p>Individuals with strong communication skills and client-facing experience</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated individuals who thrive in a performance-driven environment</p></li><li><p>Singapore Citizens or PRs, aged 21 and above (regulatory requirement)</p></li><li><p>Diploma or Degree holders (finance background not mandatory)<br /></p></li></ul><h3><strong>Professional & Educational Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>CMFAS M5, M9, and HI (or willingness to obtain)</p></li><li><p>GCE ‘A’ Levels, IB Diploma, or Diploma from a recognised Polytechnic or equivalent</p></li></ul>",
